>  hello ???      first tell us what we are working on, what year, type
> motor etc.  Type 1 motors you have to remove the fuel pump and stand.  I
> have used pencials. screwdrivers, metal rods and blind pullers that were
> made for this.  You will have to twist the drive as you pull it up. remember
> that there are washers on the bottom of the drive itself and they can fall
> off . last sign your posts as a courtesy and so we know who we are
